==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spancel
<hw>Span"cel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Perhaps
<ets>span</ets> + AS. <ets>s⟦amac⟧l</ets> a rope.]</ety> <def>A rope
used for tying or hobbling the legs of a horse or cow.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng. & Local, U.S.]</mark> <-- a different usage is in
White's "Once and future king" --> <rj><au>Grose.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spancel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spancel
<hw>Span"cel</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Spanceled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr> or <conjf>Spancelled</conjf>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Spanceling</conjf> ⟦or⟧
<conjf>Spancelling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To tie or hobble with a
spancel.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & Local, U.S.]</mark>
<rj><au>Malone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

